<HEADLINE> Bangkok Film Festival Opens </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BANGKOK, September 17 (Xinhua) -- Enthusiastic Bangkok
film-goers will be blessed with more than 50 feature films in the
next 10 days as the second annual Bangkok Film Festival kicked off
Friday evening.
</P>
<P>
Scores of shorts and documentaries are also to be shown at the
event, which is being attended by 23 foreign film directors and a
host of international actors.
</P>
<P>
The event will also feature seminars which touch upon various
topics related to the film industry.
</P>
<P>
Apart from some well-known feature films, Brian Bennett, the
festival's director, expects the shorts, documentaries and 16 mm
feature films will also draw a large number of movie-goers.
</P>
<P>
The awards ceremony will be held on September 26, when the
festival is scheduled to end. 
</P>
</TEXT>
