<HEADLINE> At Least 27 Killed in Fighting in S. Somalia </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MOGADISHU, September 17 (Xinhua) -- At least 27 people were
killed and a dozen wounded in fierce fightings Friday morning in
southern Somalia between the Ethiopian backed breakaway faction of
the Somali National Front (SNF) and the SNF main stream.
</P>
<P>
According to independent sources from Garbaharrey town, the
SNF main stream, led by Omar Hajji Masalleh, launched the attack
in the early morning for the control of the regional capital,
Garbaharrey, in the border Gedo region and targeted the defectors'
positions.
</P>
<P>
Eyewitnesses contacted on the VHF radios said the SNF main
stream forces, which had been chased out of the town four days
ago, were equipped with heavy portable machine guns,
rocket-propelled grenades and assault rifles, while the breakaway
faction resorted to five battle wagons.
</P>
<P>
The defeated breakaway forces are reported to have fled to Luq
town where Ethiopian forces are in control since the beginning of
this year. According to eyewitnesses, no Ethiopian forces were
involved in the fighting.
</P>
<P>
There has been no word as yet from the side of the breakaway
SNF faction, which has been in close relation with the Ethiopian
forces. However, there are reports indicating that Buraleh's
forces are now regrouping for counter- attack.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, the combined forces of the Rahanwein Resistance Army
(RRA) and the Digil Salvation Army (DSA) on one side and those of
Hussein Mohamed Aidid on the other went into clashes outside the
town of Qoryoley, about 120 kilometers south of Mogadishu.
</P>
<P>
According to sources from the region, more than nine people
were killed and at least 15 others wounded as the RRA and DSA
forces tried to take the town from the hand of Aidid's forces, who
since the beginning of this month have been digging defensive
trenches.
</P>
<P>
However, none of the two sides has gained any territories in
the fighting.  
</P>
</TEXT>
