<HEADLINE> Belgium Offers Financial Assistance to Tunisia </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TUNIS, September 17 (Xinhua) -- Tunisia and Belgium on Friday
signed an accord under which the latter will offer the former 3.3
million dinars (a U.S. dollar equals 1.10 dinars) in aid for the
rehabilitation of Tunisia Southern Lake.
</P>
<P>
The document was signed by Director of the European Department
of the Tunisian Foreign Ministry Anwar Belrays and Belgian
Ambassador to Tunisia John Francoin, according to the
Tunisia-Africa News Agency.
</P>
<P>
The assistance is part of Belgium's contribution to the project of
rehabilitating the banks of Tunisia Southern Lake. It is the third
batch of the 10 million-dinar contribution to the project.
</P>
<P>
Among the other contributors to the project are the Netherlands
that will offer 15.2 million dinars and the European Investment
Bank, 50 million dinars. 
</P>
</TEXT>
