<HEADLINE> African Ministers to Meet in Zimbabwe </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HARARE, September 17 (Xinhua) -- African local government
ministers will gather in Zimbabwe next week for a four-day
conference, seeking ways of transforming local authorities into
engines of local and national development.
</P>
<P>
Zimbabwean Local Government and National Housing Minister John
Nkomo told reporters in Harare on Friday, "The conference aims at
reviewing factors influencing the sharing of resources between
local and central government"
</P>
<P>
He said the conference set indicative criteria for enhancing
decentralization, democratization and good management practices
like transparency and accountability.
</P>
<P>
More than 70 delegates of 15 countries will attend the
conference. 
