<HEADLINE> Zimbabwe Blasts Congolese Rebels  for Violating </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HARARE, September 17 (Xinhua) -- Zimbabwe accused Friday the
Rebels in the Democratic Republic of the Congo (DRC) for
"systematically violating" the cease-fire agreement to provoke the
allied forces.
</P>
<P>
Zimbabwean Defense Ministry charged the rebels for looting
foodstuffs and domestic animals and abducting and killing
civilians.
</P>
<P>
The ministry spokesman Chancellor Diye said in a statement that
the rebels have killed several civilians in Kasai province last
week and shot at routine ration re-supply aircraft.
</P>
<P>
"The systematic attacks are probably meant to force the allied
forces to react so that they can claim that the allied forces have
breached the cease- fire and hence resume their military
offensives to gain more territory," he said.
</P>
<P>
Zimbabwe, Angola, Chad and Namibia have been fighting alongside
DRC President Laurent Kabila's soldiers to crash Rwandese and
Ugandan backed rebellions. 
</P>
