<HEADLINE> Final Status Talks Highly Delicate, PLC Says </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
RAMALLAH, September 17 (Xinhua) -- The final status talks
between the Palestinians and Israel are highly delicate and
sensitive, said Chief of the Palestinian Legislative Council Ahmed
Qureia (Abu-Alaa) Thursday.
</P>
<P>
Abu-Alaa made the remarks in his opening address to the
Palestinian Expert Conference on Final Settlement in Ramallah, the
West Bank.
</P>
<P>
The interim stage was the outcome of a political rally on the
Arab, regional and international arenas under the new
international situation following the second Gulf War, he said,
stressing that the peace process in the Middle East can not
succeed without the rules and provisions of the U.N. resolutions.
</P>
<P>
Abu-Alaa summed up the targets of the Palestinian people as the
termination of the three-decade Israeli occupation, the removal of
all Jewish settlements, the return of all Palestinians in exile,
and the founding of an independent Palestinian state with
Jerusalem as its capital as well as integration with the Arab
nation.
</P>
<P>
He underlined the importance of complete separation between the
interim stage and the final status talks, and halting the
settlement activity.
</P>
<P>
Organized by the International Organization for Dialog and
Democracy, the three-day conference is chaired by Hanan Ashrawi,
member of the the PLC and deals with issues of the final status
talks. 
</P>
</TEXT>
