<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Chirac Greets Algeria's Referendum Success </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
PARIS, September 17 (Xinhua) -- French President Jacques Chirac
Friday congratulated his Algerian counterpart, Abdelaziz
Bouteflika, on the success of Algeria in holding a referendum on
national reconciliation.
</P>
<P>
The Elysee presidential palace said that Chirac called the
referendum "a success for Algeria on the road of peace."
</P>
<P>
"The two presidents have renewed their common call for the
development of bilateral relations and coordination between the
two countries," said the same source.
</P>
<P>
The Algerian press agency said that Chirac praised the Algerian
people for their "great patience and their commitment to human
ideals by giving an agreement of concord between the children of
the country who cannot be divided."
</P>
<P>
The Algerians voted overwhelmingly for a law of national
reconciliation Thursday seeking an end to seven years of civil
war. 
</P>
