<HEADLINE> URGENT: Clinton Announces Easing Sanctions Against DPRK </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WASHINGTON, September 17 (Xinhua) -- U.S. President Bill
Clinton has decided to ease sanctions against the Democratic
People's Republic of Korea (DPRK), allowing more trade between the
two countries.
</P>
<P>
The measure, the first since the end of the Korean War in 1953,
will allow most consumer goods to be available for export to DPRK
and will allow the import of DPRK goods, White House spokesman Joe
Lockhart said Friday. 
</P>
