<HEADLINE> DPRK's Economy Better This Year: Premier </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
PYONGYANG, September 17 (Xinhua) -- The economic situation of
the Democratic People's Republic of Korea (DPRK) has turned better
in the first half of this year, with a 20 percent rise in
industrial output compared with the same period last year, Premier
Hong Songnam said Friday.
</P>
<P>
Some 4,000 firms have resumed operation and the overall
situation of agriculture is better than last year despite natural
disasters, Hong said when meeting a Chinese delegation led by
Deputy Minister of Foreign Trade and Economic Cooperation Chen
Xinhua.
</P>
<P>
Hong told his guests that progress has been made in industrial
and agricultural production. Although there still exists many
difficulties, Hong said, the DPRK people have confidence and
determination to build their country into a strong socialist
nation.
</P>
<P>
During the talks, Hong also highly praised the friendship
between China and the DPRK, promising to make further efforts to
develop the "special" friendship.
</P>
<P>
Commenting on Lee Teng-hui's "two-states" remark, Hong believed
that the Chinese people will surely realize their reunification
aspiration, which he said can never be obstructed by anyone.
</P>
<P>
In his part, Chen thanked the DPRK for its support to China's
policies and expressed his pleasure over the achievements made by
the DPRK people. 
</P>
</TEXT>
