<HEADLINE> Over 75% Mozambican Voters Registered </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MAPUTO, September 17 (Xinhua) -- Mozambique's voter
registration ended Friday, with around three quarters of the
potential electorate registered.
</P>
<P>
According to the latest figures from the Electoral
Administration Technical Secretariat, around 6.2 million out of an
estimated 8.3 million people above the voting age of 18 have
registered.
</P>
<P>
But that figure refers to data collected up until September 11,
and registration brigades in remote areas have not been able to
communicate their latest figures to the secretariat. Thus, the
real number of registered voters is certain to be higher than 6.2
million.
</P>
<P>
The number of people registered in 1994 for the country's first
multi- party presidential and parliamentary elections was
6,396,061.
</P>
<P>
If the final figure from this year's exercise is lower than
that, it would be regarded as a failure.
</P>
<P>
Some of the minor political parties, notably those in the
Mozambique United Opposition coalition, have demanded that voter
registration period be extended. But there seems no chance that
this demand will be granted.
</P>
<P>
Extending voter registration to September 30, as the coalition
demands, would throw the entire electoral timetable out of joint,
thus making it impossible to hold the elections on the scheduled
dates of December 3-4.
</P>
<P>
The publication of the final results from the registration is
scheduled for October 3. 
</P>
</TEXT>
