<HEADLINE> Pak-China Ties Pivotal for Regional Peace: Minister </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ISLAMABAD, September 18 (Xinhua) -- Pakistani Information
Minister Mushahid Hussain Saturday said Pakistan has always held
that its relationship with China is pivotal for peace in the
region.
</P>
<P>
Pakistan's "strong, stable and strategic ties" with China will
further expand in the 21st century, said Mushahid while addressing
a seminar on "New China in the 21st Century".
</P>
<P>
As part of the Pak-China Friendship Week launched by the
Pakistani government Saturday, the seminar was jointly organized
by the Institute of Regional Studies and the Institute of
Strategic Studies.
</P>
<P>
Mushahid described the Pak-China relationship as a model among
third world countries and said it will further deepen and become
more multi-dimensional in the next century.
</P>
<P>
He appreciated China's consistent foreign policy, saying that
the country has always upheld U.N. principles and its stands on
various issues have been in consort with international norms.
</P>
<P>
China, he said, pursues a policy of non-interference in the
internal affairs of other countries and is firmly opposed to both
"regional and global hegemonism."
</P>
<P>
Mushahid appreciated the statesmanship and sagacity of the
Chinese leadership for managing a peaceful handover of Hong Kong
and felicitated China on the forthcoming return of Macao.
</P>
<P>
Speaking on the occasion, Chinese Ambassador to Pakistan Lu
Shulin reiterated his country's policy of further consolidating
its close relationship with Pakistan, stating that China will
always remain a most reliable friend of Pakistan.
</P>
<P>
The Chinese government and the Chinese people highly value the
traditional friendship with Pakistan, Lu said, adding that the two
countries will enjoy firm friendship and stability in the 21st
century.
</P>
<P>
"It is a firmly set policy for China to further consolidate and
develop our friendship and cooperation. This policy will never
change. China will, as always, remain the most reliable friend of
Pakistan," said the ambassador.
</P>
<P>
Delivering their speeches at the seminar, defense and
international relations experts said the deep friendship between
Pakistan and China not only serves the interests of the two
countries but also contributes to regional peace and global
stability. 
</P>
