Jilin unveiled a memorial today to victims of the September 18
Incident.
</P>
<P>
Today was the 68th anniversary of the incident, which was the
beginning of the Japanese invasion of the city of Shenyang and the
move towards occupying the entire Northeast.
</P>
<P>
The memorial is in the doorway of an exhibition hall in the
palace of the puppet emperor of Manchuria.
</P>
<P>
The hall has pictures of the atrocities commited by the
Japanese troops. It opened to public in 1982 and has had some four
million visitors since then.
</P>
<P>
