<HEADLINE> Suspects Arrested for Bombing in Iran </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TEHRAN, September 18 (Xinhua) -- Several people have been
detained in connection with Thursday's fatal bombing attack in
northeastern Iran, the Tehran Times newspaper reported Saturday.
</P>
<P>
No other details of the arrest were disclosed by the newspaper.
</P>
<P>
Two people were killed and 10 others injured when a time bomb
hidden in a garbage cart exploded at the shrine of Shiite Muslim
saint Imam Reza in the holy city of Mashhad at 15:00 hours local
time (1230 GMT) Thursday.
</P>
<P>
Iranian media identified the two dead as a municipal garbage
collector and a pilgrim visiting the shrine in Mashhad, 900
kilometers northeast of the capital Tehran.
</P>
<P>
The shrine is visited by hundreds of Muslim pilgrims every
day. 
</P>
