<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Private Sector Trade Through Shanghai Port Increasing Dramatically </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHANGHAI, September 18 (Xinhua) -- Imports and exports by China
's private sector at the port of Shanghai were worth 75.34 million
U.S. dollars for the January to August period, or 6.5 times the
amount for the same period last year, according to official
statistics.
</P>
<P>
For the first eight months, private businesses in China
exported 66.49 million U.S. dollars worth of goods and imported 8.
85 million U.S. dollars worth here, or 5.3 times and 7.9 times
more than last year's amount respectively on a year-on-year basis.
</P>
<P>
The rapid increase has been attributed to a new Foreign Trade
and Economic Cooperation Ministry policy at the beginning of the
year, allowing some private enterprises to handle their own export
and import business directly.
</P>
<P>
Shanghai Customs officials said that they will provide the same
preferential policies for the private sector as they do for state-
owned enterprises.
</P>
<P>
They also said that at present the market for private sector's
exports through the Shanghai port is mainly centered in India,
Italy and the United States. Hence, there is more room for
development, they added. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
