<HEADLINE> Kiefer Wins President's Cup Tennis </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MOSCOW, September 18 (Xinhua) -- Nicolas Kiefer of Germany
Saturday defeated George Bastl of Switzerland in the final to win
the fourth ATP Tour title of his career in the 475,000 U.S.
dollars President's Cup in Tashkent, Uzbekistan.
</P>
<P>
Kiefer, the 22-year-old third seed, eliminated unseeded
qualifier Bastl 6-4, 6-2.
</P>
<P>
The German had previously won titles in Toulouse, France, in
1997 and in Tokyo and Halle, Germany, earlier this year.
</P>
<P>
Kiefer is currently 13th in the world rankings and in line for
a top 10 spot.
</P>
<P>
Bastl, who is ranked 154th in the world, began the match by
twice breaking Kiefer's serve before the German wore him down to
win in 85 minutes. 
</P>
