<HEADLINE> Beijing Tearing Down Billboards </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, September 18 (Xinhua) -- City officials announced
today that Beijing has dismantled 90 percent of the illegal
advertisements and billboards along its major thoroughfares.
</P>
<P>
Wang Guangtao, deputy mayor of Beijing, said that the move was
meant to provide a cleaner environment for the celebrations to
mark the 50th anniversary of the founding of the People's Republic
on October 1. He said that many of the billboards ruined the image
of the Chinese capital and had a bad effect on traffic.
</P>
<P>
The billboards were mainly along the Avenue of Eternal Peace
and the Second and Third Ring Roads, Wang said, and some other
offensive signs will be pulled down soon.
</P>
<P>
He said that a city management committee will be responsible
for approving all outdoor advertisements in future.  
</P>
