<HEADLINE> French Senate Delegation Leaves Yunnan for Beijing </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KUNMING, September 18 (Xinhua) -- The French Senate delegation,
headed by its president Christian Poncelet, ended their five-day
visit to the southwestern Chinese province of Yunnan and left here
today for Beijing to continue their China visit.
</P>
<P>
During their stay here, Poncelet and his party visited a
college and a museum, and attended a ceremony for the France Hall
in the '99 World Horticultural Exposition.
</P>
<P>
Li Jiating, governor of Yunnan Province, met with the
delegation. Poncelet said France will work harder to promote
existing friendship between the two sides. 
</P>
</TEXT>
