<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Long Chinese Cableway Built in South China </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HAIKOU, September 18 (Xinhua) -- A 2,138-meter long cableway
has been built to Monkey Island on Hainan Province in south China.
</P>
<P>
Monkey Island is the only tropical island nature reserve for
macaque monkeys in China. There are 2,500 of the animals living on
the island.
</P>
<P>
The cableway was built by the Wuhan Sante Cableway Co. and the
U.S. International Cableway Co. at a cost of 43 million yuan (
about 5 million U.S. dollars).
</P>
<P>
The cableway allows 450 people to move across per hour.
</P>
<P>
Trainers are busy training the monkeys for a performance on
National Day, on October 1.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
