<DATE_TIME> 1999-09-18 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> S. Lankan President Condemns Tamil Rebels' Massacre </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
COLOMBO, September 18 (Xinhua) -- Sri Lankan President
Chandrika Kumaratunga Saturday condemned the massacre of at least
51 Sinhalese villagers by Tamil rebels of the Liberation Tigers of
Tamil Eelam (LTTE) in the east of the country.
</P>
<P>
The president said she was saddened to hear the killing of
civilians in three villages in the Amparai area as the government
is doing everything possible to stop the ongoing war and to bring
peace to the island nation.
</P>
<P>
Kumaratunga expressed her condolence on behalf of herself and
the government to the families of the victims who were killed in
the small hours of Saturday.
</P>
<P>
Minister of Rehabilitation M.H.M. Ashraff has ordered that an
allowance of 10,000 rupees (140 U.S. dollars) be paid to each
victim's family.
</P>
<P>
The attack followed Tamil rebels' accusation that the Sri
Lankan Air Force had killed 22 Tamil refugees in air strikes on a
northeastern village last Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
Deputy Minister of Defense General Anuruddha Ratwatte visited
the scene of tragedy Saturday afternoon. He ordered the security
units to set up new army camps in the area and to strengthen the
security arrangements.
</P>
<P>
The LTTE rebels have been fighting for a separate homeland for
minority Tamils in Sri Lanka's north and east since 1983. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
