<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Chinese Medals for Nuclear Scientists and Satellite Pioneers </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, September 18 (Xinhua) -- The Central Committee of the
Chinese Communist Party (CPC), the State Council and the Central
Military Commission said in a decision today that they were
awarding medals to 23 scientists who made China's first atomic
bomb, its first H-bomb, and its first satellite.
</P>
<P>
The nuclear bomb and satellite development were some of the
greatest achievements of the past 50 years, something the whole
Chinese nation feels proud of, the decision said.
</P>
<P>
China detonated its first atomic bomb on October 16, 1964 and
its first H-bomb on June 17, 1967. On April 24, 1970, it put its
first satellite into orbit. These successes demonstrated the
creativity of the Chinese and had a far-reaching effect in China
and abroad and laid a solid foundation to improve China's global
status, it said.
</P>
<P>
In the process, a legion of excellent scientists and
researchers was produced, who have made great contributions to the
country's hi-tech developments and industries, it said.
</P>
<P>
The awarding of meritorious service medals for these
specialists on the eve of the 50th anniversary of the People's
Republic of China will increase Chinese people's revolutionary
spirit and support the traditions and help implement the strategy
of revitalizing the nation and increasing military strength
through science and technology, the decision said. It asked the
nation to learn from these people, to rally around the CPC Central
Committee with Jiang Zemin at its core, and to strive to be more
successful in the reforms, opening up, and modernization. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
