<DOCNO> XIE19990918.0105 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1999-09-18 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Runner Lan Lixin Wins Second Gold in City Games </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
XI'AN, China, September 18 (Xinhua) -- Runner Lan Lixin, a
disciple of coach Ma Junren, took her second gold medal in the
fourth Chinese City Games here on Saturday.
</P>
<P>
As the track and field competitions concluded, two Asian junior
records were surpassed in the Chinese City Games in both the women
's pole vault and the women's 4x400m relay with neither Asian nor
world marks.
</P>
<P>
Lan, who triumphed in the 1,500 meters on Thursday, enjoyed her
clear advantage by taking the women's 5,000 meters in 15:29.25,
but her winning mark is still far behind the world mark of 14:28.
09 set by her compatriot Jiang Bo in October, 1997.
</P>
<P>
"Our runners are a competitive group," said Lan Lixin, 20,
world 1,500m junior champion who clocked 4:10.05 in France in July,
1998," Coach Ma has urged us to run for the gold medal by
displaying our strength on the track."
</P>
<P>
The men's 5,000m race was also won by Ma's disciple Li Aiguo,
who was eventually disqualified as he stepped upon the shoe of his
opponent in the final sprint.
</P>
<P>
However, of the 43 gold medals offered in the athletics
competitions, at least five disciplines coached by Ma Junren stand
atop the podium.
</P>
<P>
The women runners from Dalian, Liaoning province, remain the
dominating force in the middle and long-distance races as they
took the top two places in the 1,500 meters wherein seven runners
entered the 12-member final.
</P>
<P>
"Our athletes have displayed their strength on the overall
level, and we hope for more good results in future in the world
with our scientific training and administration," said Shan
Xiutang, assistant director of the Chinese Athletics
Administrative Center.
</P>
<P>
Ma Junren, who attended the City Games as an observer, stole
the limelight in the world track arena in 1993 when his women
disciples took titles in the 1993 world championships in Stuttgart,
Germany with two games records.
</P>
<P>
In September, 1993, three world records were created by his
women runners, including Wang Junxia and Qu Yunxia, in the 1,500m,
3,000m and 10,000m races at the seventh Chinese National Games in
Beijing. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
