<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Pakistan FM Stresses "One China" Policy </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ISLAMABAD, September 18 (Xinhua) -- Pakistani Foreign Minister
Sartaj Aziz Saturday reiterated that Pakistan will continue to
pursue "One China" policy and extend as ever its support to China
on the issues of human rights and Tibet.
</P>
<P>
During a meeting with a visiting Chinese media delegation, Aziz
said it has been more than two years since Hong Kong's peaceful
return to China, and Macao will also enjoy its reunion with the
motherland.
</P>
<P>
"These are two giant leaps towards the cause of peaceful
reunification of the Chinese nation," said Aziz.
</P>
<P>
Aziz underlined the strategic dimension of mutually cooperative
relationship between Pakistan and China and said that recent
"strategic developments" in the region had further fortified it.
</P>
<P>
Aziz also elaborated Pakistan's position on the Comprehensive
Test Ban Treaty and expressed concern over the implications of the
Indian draft nuclear doctrine for the region and the world.
</P>
<P>
Underlining the centrality of the Kashmir issue, Aziz
emphasized the need for the resolution of the dispute through
peaceful dialogue.
</P>
<P>
Referring to the special celebrations planned by the Pakistani
government on the 50th anniversary of the founding of the People's
Republic of China, Aziz said the Pakistani people shared the joy
and pride of their Chinese brothers on this momentous occasion.
</P>
<P>
Appreciating China's global profile, the foreign minister
underscored the leading role that China has currently assumed in
the developing world.
</P>
<P>
He praised the Chinese leadership for their wisdom in charting
the course for modern China. 
</P>
</TEXT>
