<HEADLINE> Xinhua Article on Continued Fight Against Falun Gong </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, September 18 (Xinhua) -- The Xinhua News Agency, in a
commentator's article today, says that China needs to be
completely successful in the fight against the Falun Gong cult.
</P>
<P>
So far, there has been some success in the struggle against Li
Hongzhi and his illegal organization and the majority of Falun
Gong practitioners in China have severed ties with the group, the
article says. But people also need to be aware of the fact that
although the social tumor of Falun Gong has been removed, viruses
have not been fully destroyed and are still attacking society, it
says.
</P>
<P>
A small number of Falun Gong core members have not reconciled
themselves to their failures and are attempting to oppose the
government, society, and the public, the article says, and the
struggle against the organization is a serious political fight
that could be long and complicated.
</P>
<P>
While the education and transforming of the majority of Falun
Gong practitioners continues, people should do their best to
isolate and attack Li Hongzhi and other core members and punish
them in accordance with the law, it says.
</P>
<P>
Stability is in the fundamental interest of the country,
especially when the nation is preparing to celebrate the 50th
anniversary of the People's Republic of China, it says. So people
need to be vigilant against the hidden dangers left by the Falun
Gong organization and take prompt and resolute action to nip them
in the bud and be completely successful in the fight against the
organization, it concludes. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
