<HEADLINE> Conference On Conservation And Development In Southwest China </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KUNMING, September 18 (Xinhua) -- A Leadership Conference on
Conservation and Development in the Cities of Kunming and Lijiang
in southwest China's Yunnan Province, September 13-18, attracted
specialists and observers from China, the United States, Great
Britain, Germany, the Netherlands, Australia, New Zealand, the
Republic of Korea, the Philippines, Japan, Indonesia, Thailand,
Vietnam, and Hongkong region.
</P>
<P>
The participants said that the coordinated and balanced
development of national cultures, ecology, environment, and
economy are the most important way to interact between man and
nature.
</P>
<P>
Some said they value Yunnan's initiative in adopting the
general policy of becoming a great province of national cultures,
identifying specifically its diversity, nature, and culture as a
basis for development.
</P>
<P>
They also said that there needs to be a scientific approach in
carrying out projects, avoiding short-term profits, and with
adequate laws, regulations, and trained personnel for conservation.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
