<HEADLINE> PECC Trade And Investment Exposition in Northern Chinese City </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TIANJIN, September 18 (Xinhua) -- Today was the final day of
the first international trade and investment exposition of the
Pacific Economic Cooperation Council (PECC), in the coastal
Chinese city of Tianjin.
</P>
<P>
It attracted over 355 enterprises from 28 countries regions and
from 17 provinces, municipalities and autonomous regions in China
for the past five days. There were symposia on economic
development in the Pacific region and trade and investment
discussions by member countries.
</P>
<P>
Representatives from 55 foreign businesses also discussed
cooperation with Chinese counterparts, resulting in trade and
investment agreements worth 300 million U.S. dollars, organizers
said.
</P>
<P>
The exposition has played a role in promoting trade and
economic cooperation among Pacific countries and regions, they
said. It was sponsored by the Chinese Ministry of Foreign Trade
and Economic Cooperation and the Tianjin government.
</P>
<P>
The next PECC exposition is expected to be held by Hong Kong.
</P>
</TEXT>
