<HEADLINE> Nigeria Advised to Accord Tourism Priority </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LAGOS, September 18 (Xinhua) -- Nigerian Government has been
advised to accord tourism development priority as a means of
boosting its foreign exchange earnings, reported Vanguard, a
leading Nigerian newspaper Saturday.
</P>
<P>
The chairman of the Hotel and Personal Services Employers
Association, Pastor Sam Alamutu stated this in Lagos Thursday
during a presentation of bursary awards to some college students
majoring in Tourism or Catering to mark the association's 20th
anniversary, reported the paper.
</P>
<P>
He said, "with Nigeria beginning to make a mark in democracy,
there is no doubt that the hospitality industry will enjoy a
boost."
</P>
<P>
She said to promote tourism, the Lagos state government has
developed relaxation centres such as the Eko Tourist Beach Resort
and Amusement Park and Akodo, Ibeju Lekki local government and
the Badagry Maina recreation centre. 
</P>
