<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Japanese Invasion Museum Reopens In Northeast China </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHENYANG, September 18 (Xinhua) -- The September 18 Museum,
which records the Japan's invasion of China in the 1930s reopened
today in the capital of northeast China's Liaoning Province after
having been renovated.
</P>
<P>
September 18, 1931, when Japanese troops in northeastern China
began their attacks on the Chinese army and then occupied
Heilongjiang, Jilin and Liaoning provinces, is regarded as a
humiliating day in China.
</P>
<P>
Six years later, they began to invade other parts of China
resulting in a war that lasted 8 years.
</P>
<P>
President Jiang Zemin has provided the calligraphy for the
museum's name, which occupies a 31,000-sq.m. space on the site of
the opening shots. It has eight halls with historical documents,
photos and other materials on display.
</P>
<P>
The renovation cost a whopping 130 million yuan (about 16
million U.S.dollars).  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE19990918.0120 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1999-09-18 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Chinese Women Entrepreneurs Becoming More Professional </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, September 18 (Xinhua) -- A management and marketing
book compiled by the All-China Women's Federation (ACWF) and
United Nations Industry Development Organization (UNIDO) was
issued here today.
</P>
<P>
It will be used as a textbook in a management training package
to improve the management experise of Chinese women managers in
village and township enterprises.
</P>
<P>
An ACWF official said that, in 5 years of using the package
method, Chinese women entrepreneurs become more professional.
There are 4 million women working in village and township
enterprises in China, or 40 percent of the employees in these
enterprises.
</P>
<P>
More than 120 women entrepreneurs from Beijing, Hebei and
Shangdong provinces have been trained by the training package
method. They all say that modern management is essential to the
development of their own enterprises. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
