<HEADLINE> Eximbank Supports China's Shipbuilding </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, September 18 (Xinhua) -- The China Export and Import
Bank (Eximbank) today signed a credit agreement for 1.152 billion
yuan with the China State Shipbuilding Corp. (CSSC) and China
Shipbuilding Trading Co., Ltd. (CSTC).
</P>
<P>
The credit will be used to support the export of eight bulk
carriers totaling 600,000 dwt. An Eximbank spokesman said that, as
one of the State's policy banks, his bank has always supported
exports of ships, machinery, electronics, and equipment.
</P>
<P>
Eximbank was founded 5 years ago. Since then it has granted 17.
7 billion yuan in loans to support the export of ships, accounting
for 25 percent of its total loans.
</P>
<P>
Its loans have benefited exports of 402 ship, with a total
capacity of 7.33 million dwt.
</P>
<P>
CSSC is a large State-owned complex that was formed last July 1.
Its subsidiaries include shipyards, scientific research institutes,
and share-holding companies. It has orders for 1.265 million dwt
of ships from overseas.
</P>
<P>
CSTC is one of CSSC's subsidiaries. It has used 8.6 billion
yuan worth of Eximbank loans to export 97 ships.
</P>
<P>
The spokesman said that the China Ocean Shipping Companies (
HongKong) Group is having the ships built with the Eximbank loans
support. 
</P>
</TEXT>
