<TEXT>
<P>
NEW DELHI, September 18 (Xinhua) -- At least 36 people,
including 22 security personnel, were killed Saturday in
poll-related violence in the Indian states of Bihar and Andhra
Pradesh and the Kashmir valley.
</P>
<P>
Twenty-nine people, including 20 policemen and a magistrate,
were killed and 25 others injured during Lok Sabha polling in 19
constituencies in Bihar.
</P>
