<HEADLINE> Forum on Science Held in HK to Mark National Day </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, September 18 (Xinhua) -- A forum on the development
of science and technology in China and the future of Hong Kong was
held Saturday in the Hong Kong Space Museum.
</P>
<P>
At the invitation of the Hong Kong Preparatory Committee of
Scientific and Technological Circles (HKPCSTC), three renowned
scientists from China's mainland delivered reports on the latest
development of space technology, information industry and medicine
in China.
</P>
<P>
The forum, organized by the HKPCSTC which has a membership of
over 230 people from various fields of science and technology in
Hong Kong, is part of the celebration of the 50th anniversary of
the founding of the People's Republic of China.
</P>
<P>
Long Lehao, deputy director of the China Research Institute of
Rocket Technology, gave an account of the development of China's
Long March rockets, while Zhang Haimen, executive member of the
China Society of Electronics, and Lu Shengdun, a professor working
with the Chinese Academy of Medicine, spoke of the great
achievements China has made in the electronic industry and
medicine over the past 50 years.
</P>
<P>
The program for the celebration of the National Day on October
1 worked out by the preparatory committee also includes a grand
gathering on September 23 which will be attended by senior
officials from the central and local governments and people from
various kinds of scientific institutions. 
