<BODY>
<HEADLINE> HK Community Planting Days Draw Over 6,000 Participants </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, September 18 (Xinhua) -- More than 6,000 green
supporters joining the Community Planting Days have planted some
400 trees, as well as 13,000 shrubs and saplings in nine urban
venues of Hong Kong between May and September this year.
</P>
<P>
The Community Planting Days, organized by the Provisional Urban
Council (PUC), concluded Saturday.
</P>
<P>
The Community Planting Days have been held annually since 1993
to encourage local communities to support greening and promote
public green consciousness.
</P>
<P>
In addition to these community efforts, the PUC has targeted at
planting 600 and 900 heavy standard trees on streets and at
beaches, plus 20,000 tree saplings on stabilized slopes this year.
</P>
<P>
More planting sites are being identified and maintenance of
street trees are in progress.
</P>
<P>
Another highlight of the Green Campaign is the Green Hong Kong
Camp to be held in December. Through a diversified program of
talks, games, practical sessions and exhibitions, the public can
learn more about greening and conservation in a natural
environment.
</P>
<P>
There is also a unique opportunity to mark the millennium by
tree planting. The "Municipal Councils Millennium Tree Planting,"
to be launched between December 1999 and May 2000, will invite 2,
000 families and organizations to plant 2,000 trees in parks and
along trunk roads. 
</P>
</TEXT>
