<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Macao Hosts Symposium of Traditional Chinese Medicine </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MACAO, September 18 (Xinhua) -- A two-day international
symposium of traditional Chinese medicine was opened here Saturday
morning, which is expected to bolster academic exchanges.
</P>
<P>
Present at the symposium are more than 350 medical experts and
representatives coming from China's mainland, Taiwan, Hong Kong
and Macao, and from countries such as the United States, Canada,
Japan, the Netherlands, Portugal, Australia, Singapore, Malaysia
and the Philippines.
</P>
<P>
The participants will have extensive discussions on the topics
covering the basic theory of traditional Chinese medicine, its
blending with Western medicine and application in internal
medicine, surgery, gynecology and pediatrics.
</P>
<P>
About a dozen noted specialists in traditional Chinese medicine
will be invited to deliver lectures at the symposium.
</P>
<P>
The preparatory committee of the symposium had received 182
papers, 142 of which were edited into a book. 
</P>
</TEXT>
