<HEADLINE> Overseas Nigerians Urged to Support Motherland </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LAGOS, September 18 (Xinhua) -- Nigeria's first lady Stella
Obasanjo called on overseas Nigerians to help rebuild the country
during a trip to the United States, the Guardian reported
Saturday.
</P>
<P>
The Nigerian newspaper quoted the first lady as saying in
Washington Friday that her visit revealed that Nigeria is now
being accorded due respect by the outside world.
</P>
<P>
She owed the new attitude towards Nigeria to the return of
democracy and transparency in the new administration, and stressed
that Nigeria can take its rightful place in the comity of nations
only when it becomes an industrial country.
</P>
<P>
She told the gathering that she was in the U.S. to promote her
project known as 'childcare' trust which she said received
enormous support.
</P>
<P>
The first lady appealed to overseas Nigerians to give their
support for the initiative designed to help the less privileged
children in the country.
