<HEADLINE> Two Killed in UK's Light Aircraft Collision </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LONDON, September 18 (Xinhua) -- Two people were killed and a
third seriously injured after two planes collided near the runway
at London Luton Airport on Saturday, according to a BBC report.
</P>
<P>
An airport spokesman was quoted as saying that a small 330
Shorts cargo plane with nobody on board was parked on a stand when
the other plane, an AA5 light aircraft, crashed into it.
</P>
<P>
The two killed were trapped in the wreckage. Firefighters
sprayed foam over the area and emergency crews spent 15 minutes
cutting the men out of the wreckage but they were pronounced dead
at the scene.
</P>
<P>
The airport has reopened after all departures and arrivals
suspended temporarily. 
</P>
</TEXT>
