<HEADLINE> Nigerian Boxer Eexpelled after Failing Drugs Test </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JOHANNESBURG, September 18 (Xinhua) -- A Nigerian boxer has
been expelled from the All Africa Games after testing positive for
a banned steroid.
</P>
<P>
The head of the Supreme Council for Sport in Africa's medical
commission, James Sekajugo, said a urine test taken from
lightweight Osiobe Eneuvwedia on Tuesday had tested positive for a
steroid.
</P>
<P>
Sekajugo said: "Eneuvwedia is disqualified from the boxing
event ... and he is suspended from participating in all further
events at the Games.
</P>
<P>
"This decision will be communicated to the Amateur
International Boxing Association, which might impose further
sanctions."
</P>
<P>
Eneuvwedia was to have fought Ben Rabah of Tunisia in the
lightweight final on Saturday.
</P>
<P>
Eneuvwedia is the first athlete to be expelled from the Games
for failing a drugs test. 
</P>
