<HEADLINE> India's Foreign Currency Assets Down </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NEW DELHI, September 18 (Xinhua) -- India's foreign currency
assets (FCA) dropped by 61 million U.S. dollars to 30.318 billion
U.S. dollars during the week that ended September 10.
</P>
<P>
The latest fall followed a sharp drop of 163 million U.S.
dollars in the week that ended August 27.
</P>
<P>
According to the Reserve Bank of India's weekly statistical
supplement, FCA were marginally up by 10 million U.S. dollars
during the week that ended September 3.
</P>
<P>
The drop in FCA resulted in the total foreign exchange reserves
declining to 32.986 billion U.S. dollars. 
</P>
