<TEXT>
<P>
HUAIROU, Beijing, September 18 (Xinhua) -- World championship
leader Tommi Makinen of Finland pulled out of the China Rally
because of the suspension failure in the 16th stage on Saturday
here.
</P>
<P>
Makinen, who is seeking for his fourth consecutive world
championship, trailed Didier Auriol of France, driving a Toyota,
and Richard Burns of Britain on a Subaru at the third place before
his retirement.
</P>
<P>
The Mitsubishi is leading the world rally championship by 48
points, 10 points ahead of second-placed Auriol with three rounds
left in the 14-round championship. 
