<BODY>
<HEADLINE> UNDP Concerned over Use of Aid by Kenya </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NAIROBI, September 18 (Xinhua) -- The United Nations
Development Program (UNDP) has expressed concern over the delay by
the Kenyan government to account for 43.7 million U.S. dollars
provided by the agency.
</P>
<P>
East African Standard newspaper Saturday quoted acting country
representative Macleod Nyirongo as saying that Kenya had not
explained how funds under the 6th Country Support Program was
used.
</P>
<P>
The 43.7 million dollars aid was intended to finance capacity
building in the public sector, help improve governance and
small-scale enterprises.
</P>
<P>
Senior officials at Kenyan Finance Ministry pledged that
program and project accounts are audited as swiftly as required.
</P>
<P>
The U.N. aid agency also provided 14.1 million dollars for the
