region in less than one month. On August 27, a total of 29 people
were killed and 20 others were injured when a passenger bus and a
pick-up clashed.
</P>
<P>
On Monday, while launching the National Road Safety Week,
Tanzanian Vice- President Omar Ali Juma called for joint efforts
to bring down the level of accidents that is alarmingly high.
