<HEADLINE> 458,000 Overseas Filipinos Workers Deployed Worldwide </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MANILA, September 18 (Xinhua) -- Nearly half a million Overseas
Filipino Workers (OFWs) were deployed all over the world in the
first half of this year as the Philippine government almost
doubled the number of pre-employment orientation seminars for
prospective OFWs during the period, said an official report.
</P>
<P>
The report, which was released here by the presidential office,
said that 458,278 OFWs were deployed over the year's first
semester, as against the 452,550 persons who found overseas
employment a year earlier.
</P>
<P>
It said 359,819 of these newly deployed OFWs bagged land-based
jobs, while the remaining were sea-based workers.
</P>
<P>
"The Philippine Overseas Employment Administration has been
doubling its efforts in its information campaign and workers'
employment programs so prospective OFWs can make wise decisions
before they apply for work abroad," the report said.
</P>
<P>
The agency has almost doubled to 476 pre-employment seminars
nationwide in the first six months of the year, compared with 246
in the same period of last year, it said.
</P>
<P>
According to official figures, over 4 million OFWs are working
in 182 foreign destinations and earn the country about 6 billion
U.S. dollars a year. 
</P>
</TEXT>
