<HEADLINE> From Beiping to Beijing (1) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, September 18 (Xinhua) -- The Chinese capital, Beijing,
has become a prosperous modern metropolis in the past 50 years and
a symbol of New China.
</P>
<P>
The decision of the Chinese Communist Party Central Committee
to choose Beijing as the nation's capital provided a solid
foundation for the liberation of the whole country and the
estalishment of New China, and the Party has satisfied the people
with what it has achieved, says a former employee of the municipal
government, Ma Ju.
</P>
<P>
The city has preserved intact many historic sites that survived
artillery shells during the liberation of the city in late January
of 1949. Before the offensive was mounted, two soldiers were
dispatched to Qinghua University with a military map to look for
prominent architect Liang Sicheng, who was to be asked to mark all
the places of historic interest so as to avoid them from shelling.
</P>
<P>
The city served as the capital of 6 dynasties. It gained a new
life when the People's Liberation Army seized the city on January
31, 1949. On the morning of March 23, the CPC Central Committee
leaders Mao Zedong, Zhu De, Liu Shaoqi, Zhou Enlai and Ren Bishi
left their headquarters in the village of Xibaipo for Beijing,
which was called Beiping at that time.
</P>
<P>
A preparatory meeting of the First National Committee of the
Chinese People's Political Consultative Conference (CPPCC) was
convened in Beiping on June 15. Six panels were organized to make
preparations for the first meeting of the CPPCC National Committee
and for the formation of a democratic united government.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE19990918.0163 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1999-09-18 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> From Beiping to Beijing (2) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
The Kuomintang chose Nanjing as its capital, because of its
heavy dependence on the imperialists and its closeness to the
imperialist center Shanghai, but the People's Republic of China
did not need to select Nanjing because it is the Chinese people's
country and relies on the Chinese people, Shen Yanbing, a writer
and deputy head of Panel Six, wrote in a report to the first CPPCC
National Committee meeting.
</P>
<P>
Shen cited Beiping's political, cultural, and ideological
significance and geological advantages to convince the CPPCC
members that it would be the ideal location for the capital of New
China. He also proposed that it be renamed Beijing.
</P>
<P>
On September 27, the First Plenary Session of the CPPCC
National Committee approved the national flag design, the capital,
and the anthem, and then Beiping was renamed Beijing.
</P>
<P>
On October 1, Mao Zedong declared the Central People's
Government of the People's Republic of China founded, and a new
chapter opened in the history of the country and of Beijing.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
