<HEADLINE> At Least 56 S.Lankan Villagers Killed by Tamil Rebels </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
COLOMBO, September 18 (Xinhua) -- At least 56 Sinhalese
villagers were killed by Tamil rebels who attacked three villages
in eastern Sri Lanka in the early hours of Saturday morning,
police sources said.
</P>
<P>
The security forces have so far recovered 56 bodies from the
villages of Borapola, Bedi Rekka and Sinnawatta in Amparai, 350 km
east of Colombo, the sources said.
</P>
<P>
The sources said the Tamil rebels of Liberation Tigers of Tamil
Eelam (LTTE) had carried out these attacks in retaliation for the
Sri Lanka Air Force bombing of a crowded market place in northern
Sri Lanka on Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
The LTTE said in a statement that 22 Tamil civilians were
killed and 41 others wounded in an air raid on the village of
Puthukkudirruppu in Mullaitivu, some 290 km northeast of the
capital.
</P>
<P>
The LTTE rebels have been fighting a 16-year-old war against
the Sinhalese majority controlled-government for a separate Tamil
homeland in Sri Lanka's north and east. 
