<HEADLINE> U.N. Steps Up Food Deliveries to E. Timor </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CANBERRA, September 18 (Xinhua) -- Officials of the United
Nations Saturday stepped up the air delivery of emergency food to
displaced people in East Timor.
</P>
<P>
U.N. official David Wimhurst said in the northern Australian
city of Darwin that the U.N. planned to conduct two more flights,
dropping 20 tons of food to two areas outside the East Timor
capital Dili, following Friday's two flights over the same region.
</P>
<P>
