<HEADLINE> UAE Oil Minister Leaves for Riyadh </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ABU DHABI, September 18 (Xinhua) -- Obeid Bin Saif Al Nasir,
Minister of Petroleum and Mineral Resources of the United Arab
Emirates (UAE), left here Saturday for Saudi Arabia to preside
over the 22nd Gulf Cooperation Council (GCC) oil ministers'
meeting.
</P>
<P>
Topics to be discussed at the meeting, which will start later
Saturday in Riyadh, include evaluation of the current and future
situation of the international oil market, preparing feasibility
studies for a proposed trans-Gulf gas pipeline project and
developing the gas trade market between the GCC countries and the
European Union.
</P>
<P>
The meeting bears significance as it is being held a few days
ahead of the ministerial meeting of the Organization of Petroleum
Exporting Countries (OPEC).
</P>
<P>
It will help the GCC ministers to coordinate and exchange
points of view on the best ways to achieve stability in the
international oil market.
</P>
<P>
The GCC groups OPEC members Saudi Arabia, Kuwait, the UAE,
Qatar and independent oil producers Oman and Bahrain. 
</P>
