<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Lebanese Muslims Call for Disney Products Boycott </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIRUT, September 18 (Xinhua) -- Lebanon's highest Muslim
clerics have denounced a planned Walt Disney Co. exhibit in the
United States depicting Jerusalem as Israel's capital, calling on
Muslims and Arabs to boycott the company's products.
</P>
<P>
"This criminal Zionist Jewish firm is holding an exhibition to
prove that Jerusalem is the capital of Israel. This is no joke,"
the Al Nahar daily newspaper Saturday quoted Sheikh Mohammed
Shamseddine, head of the Higher Shiite Council, as saying.
</P>
<P>
The country's Shiite spiritual leader called on the media to
show statistics throughout the week revealing the money Walt
Disney earns from Arabs and Muslims.
</P>
<P>
"This is not millions of dollars but billions, from small toys
to advertisements and cartoons. This company has firms and shops
in every Arab city," Shamseddine said.
</P>
<P>
The Grand Mufti Sheikh Mohammed Rashid Qabbani, the country's
Sunni spiritual leaer, echoed the sentiment, calling on "Arabs and
Muslims to boycott all industrial and commercial institutions
which advertise the theme: Jerusalem, Israel's capital.
</P>
<P>
Disney spokesman Bill Warren has said the exhibit, part of a
15-month millennium celebration at the company's Florida theme
park on September 30, was designed to "acknowledge and honor the
people of Israel." 
</P>
</TEXT>
