<HEADLINE> Warriors Center Dampier Undergoes Knee Surgery </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WASHINGTON, September 17 (Xinhua) -- Already undermanned in the
middle, the Golden State Warriors likely will be without center
Erick Dampier for the start of the training camp.
</P>
<P>
The team announced on Friday that Dampier underwent successful
arthroscopic surgery on his left knee on Thursday to repair torn
cartilage, the lateral meniscus under the kneecap.
</P>
<P>
Dampier, who signed a multi-year contract in the offseason to
remain with the Warriors, suffered the injury during a recent
workout in Mississippi. Dampier is slated to start rehabilitation
immediately.
</P>
<P>
The 25-year-old will wear a brace for two weeks, at which time
he will begin a strength and conditioning program and be re-
evaluated periodically. Training camp is scheduled to start in
early October.
</P>
<P>
Acquired from Indiana in 1997, Dampier has averaged 10.7 points
and 8.3 rebounds per game in two season with the Warriors.
</P>
<P>
If Dampier is sidelined for an extended period of time, Adonal
Foyle likely would fill in at center. In two years with Warriors,
Foyle, a 1997 first-round pick, has averaged just 2.9 points per
contest. 
</P>
</TEXT>
