<HEADLINE> Surprise Line-up at Men's Singles Final </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
GUILIN, China, September 18 (Xinhua) -- Surprise finalists Liu
Guozheng of China and Lee Chul Seung from South Korea will face
each other for the men's singles title of the China Grand Prix
Table Tennis Championships here later on Saturday.
</P>
<P>
Liu, last-minute stand-in for injury-hit former world
championship Kong Linhui, fought out a brave five-set win over his
teammate and world number nine Wang Liqin, while unseeded Lee
ensured the marquee event is an Asian affair by foiling a European
inroad from German teenager Timo Boll.
</P>
<P>
After shocking his world champion compatriot Liu Guoliang in
the tournament on Friday, Liu Guozheng went on giantkilling and
this time the victim was ITTF Pro-Tour finals champion Wang Liqin,
who lost 21-16, 14-21, 21-18, 22-24, 21-23.
</P>
<P>
Wang had been tipped to lift the title and the 12,500 U.S.
dollars cheque after men's singles field lost all its leading
players due to premature exits or abenses.
</P>
<P>
Lee saw off Boll, the conqueror of world number two Ma Lin of
China in the third round, 21-19, 21-15, 16-21, 21-15.
</P>
<P>
Top European players such as Sweden's Jan-ove Waldner, Vladimir
Samsonov of Belarus and Croatian Zoran Primorac failed to show up
at the three-day ITTF Pro-Tour event. 
</P>
</TEXT>
