<HEADLINE> Tamil Rebels' Raid Kills 50 people in Sri Lanka </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
COLOMBO, September 18 (Xinhua) -- Tamil rebels of Liberation
Tigers of Tamil Eelam (LTTE) Saturday morning raid a village in
eastern Sri Lanka, killing at least 50 villagers, informed sources
said.
</P>
<P>
The sources said the rebels also wounded about 100 people in
the village in the Amparai district, 350 kilometers east of
Colombo. 
</P>
