<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Thai Vehicle Imports Surge in August </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BANGKOK, September 18 (Xinhua) -- Thailand's imports of
foreign-made vehicles jumped by 486 percent in August from the
same period last year to 551 units, a report from the Customs
Department available here Saturday said.
</P>
<P>
According to the report, most of the imported vehicles were
from Japan.
</P>
<P>
The department collected duties totaling 393.3 million baht
(9.8 million U.S. dollars), up 347 percent from a year earlier.
</P>
<P>
Of the total, 358 units were imported from Japan, 191 from
Europe and two from the United States.
</P>
<P>
Toyota became the most popular foreign brand in August with
imports totaling 331 units. Audi topped imports from Europe with
81 units, while Mercedes-Benz followed with 64 units. 
</P>
</TEXT>
