<HEADLINE> FTAA to Sign First Batch of Customs Accords in November </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BRASILIA, September 17 (Xinhua) -- The first batch of customs
accords within the Free Trade Area of the Americas (FTAA) are
expected to be signed during a meeting of FTAA member countries
scheduled for November 3-4 in Toronto, Canada.
</P>
<P>
During the meeting, nine agreements on boosting transparency of
the FTAA negotiating process and proposed actions for facilitating
commerce among the member countries will be approved, an FTAA
senior official told reporters here Friday.
</P>
<P>
"These agreements, to be signed next November and to be in
force next year, can be considered the first FTAA concrete results,
" he said.
</P>
<P>
He added that negotiations on FTAA will be completed by the
year 2005, when tariff standards for free trade will be
established. 
</P>
</TEXT>
