<HEADLINE> 3rd Phase of Polling Begins in India's Lok Sabha Elections </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NEW DELHI, September 18 (Xinhua) -- The third phase of polling
for the 13th Lok Sabha elections began Saturday morning in 76
constituencies in five states across the country.
</P>
<P>
Simultaneously polling is held for 97 assembly seats in Andhra
Pradesh.
</P>
<P>
About 92.7 million voters will decide the electoral fortunes of
847 lok Sabha candidates, including 58 women, in the second phase.
</P>
<P>
According to the Election Commission, the average turnout for
the first two phases on September 5 and 11 was 59.33 percent --
the first phase recorded 58.17 and the second phase 60.49 percent.
</P>
<P>
Security measures have been tightened in view of violence in
the past week.
</P>
<P>
Latest polls conducted by Indian media have given the BJP-led
National Democratic alliance a clear edge after the first two
phases of polling, with the congress lagging behind. 
</P>
</TEXT>
