<HEADLINE> Sweden to Send 5-member Team to East Timor </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
STOCKHOLM, September 17 (Xinhua) -- The Swedish government
decided Friday to earmark 2.45 million Swedish krona (about 300,
000 U.S. dollars) to finance five non-combatant Swedes to be sent
to East Timor as members of the United Nations peacekeeping force.
</P>
<P>
The five Swedes, who are to stay in East Timor for four weeks,
will start for Australia Saturday to join relief workers from
other countries for the UN peacekeeping action in East Timor.
</P>
<P>
The Swedish team will be in charge of UN peacekeepers'
accommodations and communications.
</P>
<P>
The decision was made under requests from the UN Office for
Coordination of Humanitarian Affairs, the government said.
</P>
<P>
Starting this weekend, Australian troops will be leading a UN-
mandated peacekeeping force in East Timor. 
</P>
</TEXT>
