<HEADLINE> Panama Needs to Develop Closer Ties with Neighbors </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
PANAMA CITY, September 17 (Xinhua) -- Panama must get
politically and economically closer to the Central American region,
of which it is part geographically, to achieve a better economic
development, a Panamanian councilman said Friday.
</P>
<P>
Panamanian Councilman Julio Crespo said that if Panama links
itself to Central America more closely, this country will obtain a
bigger economic development and a solid political integration at a
Latin American level.
</P>
<P>
Crespo made this statement during a ceremony held here
commemorating the 178 years of the Central American countries
independence from the Spanish dominion, an event attended by high
ranking government officials and diplomatic corps.
</P>
<P>
The councilman said that Panama is an important link in that
geographical chain of Central American countries and that its
leaders must have among their goals to speed up the integration
that will permit them to share their economic and political
experiences.
</P>
<P>
Panama plays an important role, because of its geographical
position, in the development of commerce between North, Central
and South America, he said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
