<HEADLINE> Chilean Ambassador in Spain Recalled </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SANTIAGO, September 17 (Xinhua) -- The Chilean Foreign Ministry
confirmed Friday to have recalled the country's ambassador to
Spain Sergio Pizarro Mackay.
</P>
<P>
According to a press release, Pizarro Mackay was recalled by
Foreign Minister Juan Gabriel Valdes to report on diplomatic
activities in Spain.
</P>
<P>
Pizarro will meet with Valdes in New York on the occasion of
the UN General Assembly meeting to be held there next week, then
return to Madrid, said the release.
</P>
<P>
Diplomatic sources here said the recall was taking place in the
delicate period when Chile is fighting for the return of its life-
long senator Augusto Pinochet from London.
</P>
<P>
Chile insists that the courts of Spain and Britain have no
jurisdiction over Pinochet.
</P>
<P>
Pinochet, 83, has been under arrest in London since last
October 16 on the request of a Spanish judge. Spain wants him to
be extradited to its territory for trial. A hearing on the request
is to begin on September 27. 
</P>
</TEXT>
