<HEADLINE> Exiled Paraguayan Former General to Return Home </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MONTEVIDEO, September 17 (Xinhua) -- Former Paraguayan General
Lino Oviedo, who went into exile in Buenos Aires after a political
crisis in March, has decided to return home, one of his lawyers
said here on Friday.
</P>
<P>
Oviedo ordered his four lawyers to prepare a detailed report of
the juridical and political circumstances awaiting him in his
country.
</P>
<P>
Lawyer Carlos Galeano Perrone said, "Despite our opposition,
General Oviedo has the firm will of returning to Paraguay."
</P>
<P>
Oviedo went into exile on March 29 after the assassination of
Vice-president Luis Maria Argana six days earlier and the
resignation of then President Raul Cubas Grau.
</P>
<P>
His self-exile and extradition requests have adversely affected
Paraguay's diplomatic disputes with Uruguay and Argentina. The
tree countries and Brazil are members of the Southern Common
Market. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE19990918.0235 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1999-09-18 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Party Leader Congratulates Launch of New Newspaper </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, September 18 (Xinhua) -- A senior Party leader
published an article in today's "People's Daily" to congratulate
the launch of a new newspaper, "Study Times", saying that the
whole Party should attach importance to study, and be good at
study.
</P>
<P>
Hu Jintao, a member of the Standing Committee of the Political
Bureau of the Chinese Communist Party Central Committee, says that
the creation of the newspaper by the Party School of the CPC
Central Committee is of great significance, because it follows
President Jian Zemin's instructions on better studying Marxism.
</P>
<P>
The paper will serve as a "garden" for officials and
intellectuals to exchange views on study, according to Hu, who is
also President of the Party School.
</P>
<P>
Hu says that study is linked with the ups and downs of the
course of the Party, and historical lessons should be remembered
by Party members, particularly, by leading officials.
</P>
<P>
He cites many of late Chairman Mao Zedong's instructions on the
importance of study, saying that the social stability, the
development of national economy, and the achievements scored in
socialist construction are all the results that the Party is good
at study.
</P>
<P>
Hu says that Deng Xiaoping also stressed the significance of
study, which would help the Party to achieve the success of the
reform and opening up and the modernization campaign.
</P>
<P>
Because China is in a critical historical period when the
international situation is quite complicated and science and
technology are evolving so fast, the Party should attach greater
importance to study so as to catch up with the time and win people
's support, he stresses.
</P>
<P>
What the Party should study hard includes the following
categories: Marxism, Leninism, Mao Zedong Thought, Deng Xiaoping
Theory, and various modern knowledge ranging from economics to
military tactics, according to the official.
</P>
<P>
He notes that the fight against the Falun Gong cult headed by
Li Hongzhi further shows the importance of study and the
strengthening of the Party's disciplines.
</P>
<P>
He urges that the "Study Times" be run by people with political
consciousness who always adhere to the Party's line of
emancipating mind and seeking truth from facts. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
