<HEADLINE> Indonesia's Foreign Exchange Reserves Decline </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JAKARTA, September 18 (Xinhua) -- Indonesia's net foreign
exchange reserves dropped 156 million U.S. dollars to 15.6 billion
dollars as of September 15, Bank Indonesia said in its latest
weekly report, quoted by the Antara News Agency Saturday.
</P>
<P>
The drop was due to foreign debt payments, the weekly report
said, adding that net foreign exchange reserves are still above
the minimum target of 14 billion dollars set by the International
Monetary Fund (IMF).
</P>
<P>
The gross foreign exchange, which are net foreign exchange
reserves plus outstanding foreign exchange contracts, also down
170.3 million to 26.49 billion dollars. 
