<HEADLINE> Venezuelan Oil Basket Price Increases </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CARACAS, September 17 (Xinhua) -- The Venezuelan oil basket
price increased this week by 1.7 U.S. dollars to reach 20.40
dollars per barrel because of a rise in demand, the Mines and
Energy Ministry announced on Friday.
</P>
<P>
The Venezuelan oil basket average price increased this week to
13.75 dollars per barrel, 4.75 dollars above the average sale
price of nine dollars foreseen in the 1999 budget of the nation.
</P>
<P>
The prices of crude increased since the implementation on March
12 of an agreement between independent organizations and the
Organization of Petroleum Exporting Countries (OPEC) that cut
daily output by 2.1 million barrels a day. The agreement will be
in effect until next April.
</P>
<P>
Acting Mines and Energy Minister Alvaro Silva Calderon said
Thursday that output cuts will be maintained despite middlemen
pressures for OPEC to release part of the production retained
during its September 22 conference in Vienna. 
</P>
</TEXT>
