<HEADLINE> Pak-China Friendship Week Inaugurated </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ISLAMABAD, September 18 (Xinhua) -- Pak-China Friendship Week
was inaugurated here Saturday to commemorate the Golden Jubilee of
the founding of the People's Republic of China.
</P>
<P>
Talking to media on the occasion of the Pak-China Friendship
Week, Information Minister Mushahid Hussain said it reflects
multi-dimensional, substantive, strategic, warm and consistent
relationship which the two countries have enjoyed for a long time.
</P>
<P>
Briefing the media about the salient features of the week-long
comprehensive program, Mushahid said seminars, acrobatic shows,
conferences, photographic exhibitions and food festivals will be
held to mark the week.
</P>
<P>
He said three Chinese delegations including cultural troupe,
media team and a youth delegation have already arrived in Pakistan
to participate in the programs.
</P>
<P>
The Pakistani government and the people want to share these
celebrations with their Chinese friends as the two countries have
time-tested and deep rooted relationship which is a model for
others, said the minister.
</P>
<P>
Mushahid said that he will leave for China on September 26
along with a cultural delegation to participate in Chinese
celebrations. He said this is the only foreign official delegation
China has invited.
</P>
<P>
He said Pakistan has given special extra-ordinary gestures to
China by celebrating the week. Pak-China relations are on-going
process and these will be further strengthened in the coming 21st
century, he said.
</P>
<P>
Pakistan and China have commonalty of interests and both
nations are committed to the U.N. Charter, international laws and
good neighborly relations, he added. 
</P>
