<DOCNO> XIE19990918.0255 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1999-09-18 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Wall Street Stocks Rise </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NEW YORK, September 17 (Xinhua) -- Wall Street stocks moved
higher Friday mainly due to the dollar rebound against Japanese
yen.
</P>
<P>
The Dow Jones industrial average closed up 66.17 at 10,803.63.
The blue chip index fell 292.87 points in the three previous days.
</P>
<P>
Broader stock indicators were also higher. The Standard &AMP;
Poor's 500 index rose 16.94 at 1,335.42 and the technology heavy
Nasdaq composite index rose 62.90 at 2,869.62.
</P>
<P>
Stocks rallied as the U.S. dollars rebounded strongly today to
106.86 yen from 105.19 yen Thursday. The Dollar sank to 104.23 yen
Wednesday, the lowest level since the mid-May 1996, and bounced
back to 105.19 yen Thursday.
</P>
<P>
Strong dollar can entice investors into the U.S. stock market
and weak dollar will encourage traders to pull out of U.S. stocks.
</P>
<P>
The NYSE index rose 5.78 at 613.10 and the American Stock
Exchange index rose 3.64 at 794.44. The Russell 2000 index of
smaller companies rose 4.20 at 434.45.
</P>
<P>
Advancing issues outnumbered decliners by a 4-to-3 margin on
the New York Stock Exchange, with 1,691 up, 1,266 down and 577
unchanged.
</P>
<P>
NYSE volume increased to 842.63 million shares from 723.22
million in the previous session. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
